1
00:00:02,630 --> 00:00:05,050
Episode 14

2
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,470
If we

3
00:00:30,470 --> 00:00:34,050
can see each other like a habit, you want to bet on it?

4
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,920
Come to me now.

5
00:00:48,490 --> 00:00:50,180
Won.

6
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:26,940
Whoo!

7
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:49,740
Will she not be here today?

8
00:01:50,830 --> 00:01:53,920
♬ I couldn't say no ♬

9
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:56,270
It's okay if you are late.

10
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:57,290
I can wait.

11
00:01:57,290 --> 00:02:02,530
♬ The more you ask the more I love ♬

12
00:02:02,530 --> 00:02:08,840
♬ Even without any excuse ♬

13
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:15,190
♬ I can only stand and turn around ♬

14
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:22,740
♬ Please don't blame me ♬

15
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:28,120
♬ I will say what needs to be said ♬

16
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:34,550
♬ Walking while crossing paths like this ♬

17
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:41,180
♬ is a long and endless journey ♬

18
00:02:41,950 --> 00:02:48,560
♬ I'm heading toward you ♬

19
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:54,870
♬ Now I can't be stopped ♬

20
00:02:54,870 --> 00:03:00,880
♬ Turn around and look at me ♬

21
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:04,220
♬ Only time passes us by  ♬

22
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:07,580
So you did come this way, huh.

23
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:10,120
I found you.

24
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:15,500
Of course. Like I said, we always end up meeting in the end.

25
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,500
You're right.

26
00:03:36,420 --> 00:03:38,380
Were you waiting?

27
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:42,120
If I hadn't come, what were you going to do?

28
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:46,000
Is today the only day?

29
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,420
And also, did you forget that we're neighbors?

30
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:55,380
What's going on?

31
00:03:56,400 --> 00:04:01,620
I really can't hide anything from you.

32
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,440
I...

33
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:10,800
I broke up with Cha Seo Hoo.

34
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,080
So...

35
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:22,740
I need some time.

36
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:57,820
Oh Ha Na

37
00:04:58,780 --> 00:05:04,020
I think I shouldn't give her time to think.

38
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:08,200
If it were like it was in the past,

39
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:13,280
no matter what time I'd call her or go find her, I still had confidence.

40
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:18,340
I firmly believed that Oh Ha Na would always accept me.

41
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:24,340
But right now,

42
00:05:24,340 --> 00:05:29,200
I'm hesitating, and should I say I feel like I'm blocked?

43
00:05:30,420 --> 00:05:33,660
We used to call each other a lot every day.

44
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:37,240
But what if she doesn't pick up this time?

45
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:41,260
What do I do if she intentionally avoids me?

46
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,940
I...

47
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,300
I can't be staying like this.

48
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:55,100
If you are this distressed,

49
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:58,820
what about accepting President Min's suggestion?

50
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:16,800
I broke up with Cha Seo Hoo.

51
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:30,820
Even though I know Dad must have been angry and upset, he still trusted his daughter's decisions.

52
00:06:30,820 --> 00:06:32,240
I'm sorry.

53
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:36,000
And I'm sorry to my mom who always stood by my side.

54
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:40,460
Why? What was the problem?

55
00:06:40,460 --> 00:06:44,360
You said you were going to get married. Did he decide he wouldn't be able to?

56
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:48,320
Before, it was enough for me if I liked him.

57
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,780
What was important was only my feelings.

58
00:06:50,780 --> 00:06:55,300
But now, I also want to consider whether or not he can get along well with my friends and family.

59
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:59,240
Someone who not only can make me happy but also everyone around me.

60
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:03,080
Recently, I've been having these kinds of thoughts.

61
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:09,700
You must have matured as you aged, Ha Na.

62
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:12,660
Should I say that my judging criteria have changed

63
00:07:12,660 --> 00:07:16,460
to someone whom I can trust to be with me until the end?

64
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:19,600
Anyway, I'm sorry

65
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,200
for disappointing you all again.

66
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:24,800
You did not disappoint us. You dated and loved someone.

67
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:27,100
You've dealt with a lot of those things.

68
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:30,100
'The passion has cooled off' or 'I wanted simplicity'.

69
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:33,260
You can call it as such, but as you grow old and get hurt,

70
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:36,520
you will be able to see development.

71
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:40,480
Noona, you did well.

72
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:46,020
I trust you have pondered enough over this decision you've made, so I won't say more.

73
00:07:46,020 --> 00:07:50,140
You! If you'll be acting listlessly again like before,

74
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:53,100
I can't see that again! Pull yourself together.

75
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:56,600
- Do it without any mess! Alright?
- Okay.

76
00:07:56,700 --> 00:08:01,340
Wow, the quality of today's family conversation is too high. It's too hard on me.

77
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,320
Yes.

78
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:48,740
A nurse at Villa Test. A supermodel.

79
00:08:48,740 --> 00:08:50,360
A modern dancer.

80
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:53,420
No words needed for their bodies, and their average age is 21 years old.

81
00:08:53,420 --> 00:08:58,100
Above-average looks! This set-up is amazing!

82
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:02,940
Wow! Is this a three-on-three blind date? I'm jealous!

83
00:09:02,940 --> 00:09:06,460
The girls will decide on the date, so you better do your best to take off time from work by then!

84
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:07,660
I'm declining.

85
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:10,380
You can't! I already said we're going as three!

86
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:12,740
I'm not doing it.

87
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:17,520
Hey just a second, is there by any chance someone you like?

88
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:21,280
Is there really someone?

89
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:23,980
Who... Who is it?

90
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,100
Is it someone we know?

91
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:30,140
Hey! Is there?? If it's not something like that, you have no choice but to come out with us.

92
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:32,760
Yes. There is someone.

93
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:36,500
I'll be going.

94
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:38,160
No thanks for me as well.

95
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:41,700
Why you, too! Alright, if you two aren't going,

96
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:44,100
I will meet all of them!

97
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,000
Sounds like a great idea.

98
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:49,980
Sunbae, who is it really, though?

99
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:52,720
Don't try to dig too much. Move.

100
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:55,180
Just tell me who it is!

101
00:09:58,180 --> 00:10:02,460
As a thank-you-gift for your present, let's have a meal together some time.

102
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:04,760
Okay.

103
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,860
Forget it then.

104
00:10:38,020 --> 00:10:40,360
Ah, yes. It's me, President Min.

105
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:09,240
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

106
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,560
Do you think she's doing okay?

107
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:41,780
If she's not okay, we should do everything we can to make everything okay.

108
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:45,900
Well, instead of doing nothing and lying on her bed all day,

109
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:48,260
I'd say acting like that is better.

110
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:52,300
Let's go, so she can at least let go of some of her stress here at home.

111
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:56,340
It's really been a while since I've gone to your store.

112
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:43,500
After becoming single, I get to see everyone else fall in love.

113
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:47,680
I clearly feel what love is.

114
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,920
The happy feeling of deeply falling in love

115
00:12:50,920 --> 00:12:54,100
as your gaze fixes on someone.

116
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:02,260
That's not my role to play... for the time being.

117
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:09,040
Right now, it's the time for me to empty

118
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:11,860
the space within my heart.

119
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,620
Oh, my God!

120
00:13:32,170 --> 00:13:36,530
Thank you, Mom.

121
00:13:36,530 --> 00:13:39,540
Mom, please take the remaining ones upstairs.

122
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:42,090
Aigoo!

123
00:13:44,410 --> 00:13:46,890
Look forward to this. Tadah!

124
00:13:48,140 --> 00:13:49,910
Newly released goods!

125
00:13:49,910 --> 00:13:51,710
- Wow!
- I love you ,Oh Ha Na.

126
00:13:51,710 --> 00:13:53,290
It's an encouragement gift.

127
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:57,760
I prepared it for you guys who always cheered me on.

128
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:59,850
This is... a bag!

129
00:13:59,850 --> 00:14:01,440
Thank you! Ha Na, I love you!

130
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:04,610
- Look at it. They're shoes. You wear the same size as me, right?
- Thanks.
- What size do you wear?

131
00:14:04,610 --> 00:14:08,190
Hey! I don't quite feel good about this.

132
00:14:08,190 --> 00:14:10,880
We should be consoling you who broke up, but you're giving us gifts instead.

133
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:14,880
It's okay! The rest, you split it for yourselves as you see fit.

134
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,350
- Thank you!
- Thanks!

135
00:14:16,350 --> 00:14:21,790
But, since it's the second time, it's less painful, isn't it?

136
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:24,930
Hey! If you get hit and then get hit again, does it make it less painful?

137
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:29,770
But at least this time around, you gained the know-how on how to get over it, so it's a relief, right?

138
00:14:29,770 --> 00:14:34,950
Look at it. When she first broke up with Cha Seo Hoo, you couldn't even see the tip of her head and she didn't even move an inch.

139
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:38,570
But this time, doesn't she look like she's actually moving forward?

140
00:14:38,570 --> 00:14:40,700
Do I look that way?

141
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:44,260
Moving forward... I need that right now.

142
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:48,290
I fought with Chang Soo, so for the past few days, we've been in a cold war.

143
00:14:48,290 --> 00:14:49,760
But you have always been fighting.

144
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:52,290
Why? What's wrong?

145
00:14:52,290 --> 00:14:55,620
Just... I think we're just too familiar with each other.

146
00:14:55,620 --> 00:14:59,240
Novelty, anticipation and tension from the other person...

147
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,750
There are none of those things.

148
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:05,640
At one point, I suddenly hated him to death and I couldn't stand it anymore,

149
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:10,570
but because we know each other so much, it doesn't seem right to regret.

150
00:15:11,330 --> 00:15:14,460
The relationship between a man and a woman

151
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:17,070
becomes difficult as it goes on for a long time.

152
00:15:17,070 --> 00:15:20,960
It's also difficult to date and love each other right away.

153
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:25,920
♬ Not a friend, and not even a husband

154
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:29,910
Ah, seriously! Kang Na Yeong!

155
00:15:29,910 --> 00:15:33,330
- Huh? My Chang Soo really likes this!
- Omo.

156
00:15:33,330 --> 00:15:35,440
You haven't eaten this yet, right? I'm taking it with me.

157
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:38,020
Look at her, look at her. She's taking care of him anyway.

158
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:41,300
Hey, Park Jeong Mi. Put that down.

159
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:44,940
You can't eat this by yourself anyway. I'm leaving.

160
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:46,920
- There's a lot.
- Hey, come over here.

161
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:51,090
- Hey, leave that here! come here!
- Bye!

162
00:15:51,090 --> 00:15:52,910
Hey! I'm catching you today!

163
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:55,100
I have to get that back! Move!

164
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,730
Teammates!

165
00:15:57,830 --> 00:16:00,190
Alright!

166
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:03,680
Ah, Hyung. Should I tell you some big news?

167
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,070
What is it now?

168
00:16:05,070 --> 00:16:08,540
Noona  broke up with Cha Seo Hoo.

169
00:16:08,540 --> 00:16:10,090
Is that so?

170
00:16:12,090 --> 00:16:15,930
But, it's not the rabbit bastard, but Noona who asked to break up.

171
00:16:15,930 --> 00:16:20,050
What was it? She said her criteria for love has changed from the past.

172
00:16:20,050 --> 00:16:23,470
What does she mean? Did she have a change of heart, Hyung?

173
00:16:23,470 --> 00:16:25,750
That could happen.

174
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,990
Anyway, stop putting your nose in your sister's love life, Oh Dae Bok.

175
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:31,850
I really couldn't picture, for the life of me, that Noona would break up with that rabbit bastard.

176
00:16:31,850 --> 00:16:36,720
Is love changing, in other words, just getting tired of the other?

177
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:39,330
I think it's not really others' business to me.

178
00:16:39,330 --> 00:16:44,000
Oh. Your thoughts have deepened after beginning to date.

179
00:16:45,660 --> 00:16:47,710
Is your part-time job going well?

180
00:16:54,910 --> 00:16:56,540
Why?

181
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:58,850
I must have matured.

182
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:01,680
I thought it would be alright if I just inherit Father's store,

183
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:05,060
but after dating Eun Jeong, I started thinking a lot.

184
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:07,940
It's nice, but it's also desolate.

185
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:13,130
If I earn $5.80 an hour, when would I get the money to get married?

186
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:17,810
What do I earn my living with? Can I protect love if I don't have the means?

187
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:22,990
Do you remember running away from home when you were in middle school?

188
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:24,890
It was a serious runaway.

189
00:17:24,890 --> 00:17:28,520
Hey, does it make sense that you ran away from home because they said you weren't allowed to read comics?

190
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:32,040
It's not because I wasn't allowed to read that I left home. It was because they didn't allow me to draw.

191
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:34,590
That's the same thing.

192
00:17:34,590 --> 00:17:37,220
How about starting on it again?

193
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:38,410
Huh?

194
00:17:38,410 --> 00:17:40,780
It's a waste to let your skill just fall apart.

195
00:17:40,780 --> 00:17:45,130
Honestly, I was already a fan of yours since then. Your first work was...

196
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:47,940
The Journey of Jajjang Man!

197
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:50,120
See!

198
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:54,020
Start drawing again. I strongly recommend it!

199
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:58,010
Thank you. I'll think about it.

200
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:16,680
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

201
00:18:24,850 --> 00:18:27,870
You're hungry, aren't you? Let's eat.

202
00:18:27,870 --> 00:18:29,390
But you didn't call.

203
00:18:29,390 --> 00:18:32,320
Have I ever done that before coming here?

204
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:35,350
Okay, okay, okay.

205
00:18:40,380 --> 00:18:41,450
Snacks, deal!

206
00:18:41,450 --> 00:18:43,500
I am hungry.

207
00:18:45,270 --> 00:18:47,310
Come here.

208
00:18:49,390 --> 00:18:52,030
- What is that?
- What?

209
00:18:52,030 --> 00:18:56,170
Don't make that face. It's disgusting.

210
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,820
Alright.

211
00:19:01,820 --> 00:19:04,220
I'll eat it.

212
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:05,680
Eat this.

213
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:08,740
You know how to try to deter me too, Choi Won?

214
00:19:09,950 --> 00:19:12,780
I am trying my best right now.

215
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:16,620
Forget it.

216
00:19:20,040 --> 00:19:22,190
I can't live because of you, really!

217
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:43,140
That day, with the script you started writing again...

218
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:45,790
The day you sent me your script...

219
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:51,450
I had the thought of going straight to you.

220
00:19:51,450 --> 00:19:53,380
You should have come right away then.

221
00:19:56,040 --> 00:20:00,060
I felt that way up until I left the restaurant,

222
00:20:00,060 --> 00:20:04,950
but as I was walking, I started asking myself.

223
00:20:04,950 --> 00:20:08,050
Wanting to go to you... what feelings are they?

224
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:10,260
Why do I feel this way?

225
00:20:10,260 --> 00:20:13,200
I was thinking as I was walking.

226
00:20:14,050 --> 00:20:15,950
Did you find the answer?

227
00:20:17,370 --> 00:20:20,410
There were moments that I became excited  because of you.

228
00:20:28,690 --> 00:20:30,830
I like it when we are together.

229
00:20:37,680 --> 00:20:39,770
I thought it was special.

230
00:20:39,770 --> 00:20:42,990
It was also the same for you, right? It wasn't that bad.

231
00:20:44,490 --> 00:20:45,830
Yeah.

232
00:20:45,830 --> 00:20:51,100
But, for each of those moments, because of us being friends,

233
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:53,250
we ought to be careful.

234
00:20:55,600 --> 00:21:01,030
It's not an emotion that made my heart beat so fast and made me feel like I'm going out of my mind,

235
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:05,790
but it's also not just an emotion of simply concluding you are just a friend who always stays by my side.

236
00:21:14,020 --> 00:21:16,870
In order to find the answer to that,

237
00:21:16,870 --> 00:21:19,160
let's do our best together.

238
00:21:27,690 --> 00:21:30,970
Let's ask our hearts rather than our brains.

239
00:21:33,380 --> 00:21:35,580
That's being more honest.

240
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:43,350
I'm leaving!

241
00:21:51,900 --> 00:21:54,690
It's difficult. Difficult.

242
00:22:11,530 --> 00:22:14,310
Work harder, Choi Won!

243
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:21,370
A scouting offer?

244
00:22:21,370 --> 00:22:25,230
At our joint branch in Paris, France with Jumei Global.

245
00:22:25,230 --> 00:22:28,320
I recommended you to be in-charge of the marketing there.

246
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,940
Ah, I see.

247
00:22:29,940 --> 00:22:32,030
Why? You liked going to Paris for training last time

248
00:22:32,030 --> 00:22:34,870
because you thought it would be your entree into global marketing.

249
00:22:34,870 --> 00:22:37,490
Didn't you have similar hopes with China's Jumei Global as well?

250
00:22:37,490 --> 00:22:41,790
That's true, but it's an unthinkable opportunity for me.

251
00:22:41,790 --> 00:22:45,110
If it's you, it wouldn't be bad for us as well.

252
00:22:45,110 --> 00:22:48,370
We have a lot to gain sending one person.

253
00:22:48,370 --> 00:22:50,500
It is also a great opportunity for you personally.

254
00:22:51,310 --> 00:22:54,960
It is for a one-year contract for now. After that,

255
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:58,110
they will give you an option for another year.

256
00:22:59,430 --> 00:23:01,980
Your annual salary is not to be scoffed at either.

257
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:04,500
I will think about it.

258
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:31,600
The concert planning isn't bad.

259
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:35,720
It's an honor just to have you perform with me.

260
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:41,170
It is charming to perform on a non-traditional stage for a change.

261
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:45,790
I will definitely finish my concert well before I leave.

262
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:49,360
How are you doing with that person you've introduced to me before...?

263
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:52,930
We are at a bit on a cold stage...

264
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:06,220
