271
00:24:47,940 --> 00:24:54,960
♬ Over and over I miss you again  ♬

272
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:56,680
Ahh...

273
00:25:00,220 --> 00:25:03,440
If you just get the job, I can manage it awesomely

274
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:06,520
and make you a famous person.

275
00:25:06,520 --> 00:25:09,560
You should become famous with your own merits.

276
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:14,780
It is rare whether in products or people, for demand  for the object to be based on its intrinsic value.

277
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:17,800
Someone adds meaning and repackages

278
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:20,940
it into a valuable product completely different from the original.

279
00:25:20,940 --> 00:25:24,180
That is plan marketing and the strength of managing.

280
00:25:24,180 --> 00:25:26,860
Right, you are on the top in your department.

281
00:25:26,860 --> 00:25:28,860
So you are going to use that massive talent on me?

282
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:35,060
Because you are my friend whom I like  and I hope for the best for more than anyone else.

283
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:43,480
Look at me.

284
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:45,040
Why?

285
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:50,400
Turn your dream over to me.

286
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,800
I will put an extraordinary value into it.

287
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:54,720
Should I?

288
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:58,540
Global marketer. Aren't I cool?

289
00:25:58,540 --> 00:26:01,080
It suits you.

290
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:11,380
Ah, you scared me.

291
00:26:12,860 --> 00:26:16,620
- Ah...
- What were you thinking that you couldn't hear me calling you from behind?

292
00:26:17,460 --> 00:26:22,340
Just thinking about what it is that I want to do.

293
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:27,080
What do I want to do in the future. Those kinds of thoughts.

294
00:26:27,080 --> 00:26:29,960
You do that sort of thinking alone, pitifully?

295
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:32,640
There are some worries that you do alone.

296
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:38,120
If you must pick one, between your friend or lover,

297
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:42,060
I can accompany you with an appropriate reaction.

298
00:26:42,060 --> 00:26:44,620
An appropriate reaction?

299
00:26:51,380 --> 00:26:54,840
Be a lover like this.

300
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:58,460
Or be a friend just like this.

301
00:26:58,460 --> 00:27:04,260
I will walk quietly next to you, so you can be like you are alone.

302
00:27:04,260 --> 00:27:06,800
What is this, Choi Won?

303
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:10,380
But my honest feelings are...

304
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:17,500
walking for awhile like this.

305
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:24,520
This is nice! Walking like this.

306
00:27:24,520 --> 00:27:27,700
Please step away! This is weird.

307
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:30,860
Why? Why is this weird?

308
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:35,780
I am thirsty. Do you want some ice cream?

309
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:37,460
Shall we?

310
00:27:55,780 --> 00:27:57,400
This will take care of it.

311
00:27:57,400 --> 00:28:01,180
Hey. Hey, Choi Won let go!

312
00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:04,600
Let go! Hurry and let go.

313
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:10,820
You're worried about something, aren't you?

314
00:28:12,680 --> 00:28:15,180
How can I hide anything from you?

315
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:18,540
What is it that you are worrying about?

316
00:28:19,740 --> 00:28:21,980
Do you remember my dream?

317
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:25,940
Global marketer?

318
00:28:25,940 --> 00:28:31,500
Jumei Global offered me a position as a director in marketing in their Europe location.

319
00:28:31,500 --> 00:28:35,360
Is that right? The director is a big deal!

320
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:40,000
Relocation for a year and increase in salary along with great benefits.

321
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:45,000
Then you should take it.

322
00:28:46,740 --> 00:28:49,720
A great opportunity came along,

323
00:28:50,460 --> 00:28:55,240
but for some reason I am hesitating and dragging my feet.

324
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:57,780
I don't know exactly why.

325
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:02,280
It is a bit disappointing for me.

326
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:04,960
But it seems like a great opportunity for you.

327
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,860
Really?

328
00:29:06,860 --> 00:29:09,620
Yeah.  Really.

329
00:29:37,080 --> 00:29:41,740
It would have been great if we met about five-years before.

330
00:29:41,740 --> 00:29:43,600
Why?

331
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:46,700
I was quite alright then.

332
00:29:46,700 --> 00:29:49,720
My body had more elasticity than right now,

333
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:54,140
and I was more energetic and my face was more glowing than now.

334
00:29:54,140 --> 00:29:59,100
I feel bad for not being able to show you myself then.

335
00:29:59,100 --> 00:30:01,420
I told you are still pretty.

336
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:06,420
You really aren't going to have one drink of soju?

337
00:30:06,420 --> 00:30:09,360
I never drink soju.

338
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:13,160
I really don't understand you. Potato stew,

339
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:18,220
roasted eggs, and steamed corn on the cob. You are just the soju style.

340
00:30:28,120 --> 00:30:30,600
Let's go to Cha Seo Hoo's concert together.

341
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:35,140
That darn Cha Seo Hoo...

342
00:30:35,140 --> 00:30:38,680
Ahjussi! Please give me one more bottle of soju.

343
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:42,140
You've had enough. You need to get home, right?

344
00:30:42,140 --> 00:30:44,000
That darn home.

345
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:47,500
It's not like I can't wait

346
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:49,480
to go home like a virgin ghost or anything.

347
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:29,560
Mi Hyang!

348
00:31:30,420 --> 00:31:33,020
Let's stay the night together.

349
00:31:33,020 --> 00:31:35,060
Jong Hoon!

350
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:39,260
Let's go.

351
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:47,440
Jong Hoon!

352
00:31:57,140 --> 00:31:59,840
That's an offer with a lot of money noise, isn't it?

353
00:31:59,840 --> 00:32:02,600
You are right. It really is.

354
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:05,380
But why are  you hesitating about it?

355
00:32:05,380 --> 00:32:12,080
It is a great opportunity, but I am wondering if I am missing something.

356
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,880
I really don't understand it.

357
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:19,620
It isn't necessarily good just for the sake of going overseas.

358
00:32:19,620 --> 00:32:21,020
Yeah.

359
00:32:21,020 --> 00:32:26,680
At any rate, being separated from my daughter for a year

360
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:29,180
is making me feel a bit sad.

361
00:32:29,180 --> 00:32:30,980
Me too.

362
00:33:09,620 --> 00:33:12,780
Jeong Mi is obsessed with food styling these days.

363
00:33:12,780 --> 00:33:17,160
For the sake of taking one picture, she purchases expensive ingredients to make the cuisine.

364
00:33:18,420 --> 00:33:21,000
Hey. You must really earn money diligently.

365
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:26,120
Hey. As the relationship gets older, you must acknowledge

366
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:28,080
the other person's solitary time and habits.

367
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:29,960
Where did you hear that weird story?

368
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:32,200
No, that is correct.

369
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:36,160
If Jeong Mi and I were always together and didn't acknowledge each other's solitary time,

370
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:41,000
then we'd probably have already broken up or had an affair.

371
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:46,240
Being alone... is a necessity.

372
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:49,520
An old lover being alone ...

373
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:53,280
If I get into a relationship, common hobbies

374
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:56,200
and common interests will be a must for me.

375
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:59,420
Then that will make you grow tired too quickly and break up.

376
00:33:59,420 --> 00:34:03,080
Right. Let's acknowledge solitary time.

377
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:05,380
This is our lesson today. Cheers!

378
00:34:05,380 --> 00:34:07,620
Cheers!

379
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:20,500
- Sunbaenim.
- Yes?

380
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:23,800
It's lunch time. Aren't you going to eat?

381
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:26,630
It's already that time?

382
00:34:26,630 --> 00:34:29,210
Would you like to eat together?

383
00:34:30,410 --> 00:34:32,350
Yes, let's.

384
00:34:37,210 --> 00:34:41,490
I came back today from sending off my grandmother on a vacation to Europe.

385
00:34:41,490 --> 00:34:44,710
Is it alright for her age to be traveling? Aren't you worried?

386
00:34:44,710 --> 00:34:46,750
Will worrying do anything?

387
00:34:46,750 --> 00:34:49,930
She won't be able to go on any trips when she gets older, even when she wants to go.

388
00:34:49,930 --> 00:34:53,320
So, I need to send her when she wants to go.

389
00:34:55,100 --> 00:34:57,140
It's better to send her than worry about her.

390
00:34:57,140 --> 00:34:58,750
Of course.

391
00:34:58,750 --> 00:35:04,870
Before she left, in case there might be an accident, I got her an insurance policy and a health check-up.

392
00:35:06,100 --> 00:35:09,370
So Eun, you have a surprisingly bold side.

393
00:35:09,370 --> 00:35:13,830
That's why I obediently gave up on Sunbae Choi Won.

394
00:35:13,830 --> 00:35:15,000
What?

395
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:17,040
I'm just kidding.

396
00:35:18,060 --> 00:35:24,100
I don't want to live being weighed down by things I know and worrying about things I don't.

397
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:28,910
I personally think that life is too short to even just enjoy my life.

398
00:35:41,250 --> 00:35:48,400
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

399
00:35:59,460 --> 00:36:03,760
Um. What I am craving?

400
00:36:06,700 --> 00:36:11,900
Cherries and very sweet cake.

401
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:19,020
You said you were gaining weight. Yet you are wanting high calorie cake, aigoo...?

402
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:26,440
Okay. I will see you later.

403
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:33,760
Good Luck

404
00:36:33,760 --> 00:36:37,660
- Wow!
- Good Luck.

405
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:44,210
I personally think you should do the things you want to do without regrets. Go and come back.

406
00:36:44,210 --> 00:36:46,880
So you are thinking it would be better for me to go, right?

407
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:48,960
I think this way.

408
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:55,220
Oh Ha Na was scouted by a very good company and got an opportunity to do what she wants to do.

409
00:36:55,220 --> 00:36:58,520
I will schedule my flights so I can come visit you every two weeks.

410
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:00,400
That often?

411
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:03,140
You will get tired and won't come.

412
00:37:03,140 --> 00:37:07,880
Probably, right? Let's take pictures.

413
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,360
What pictures?

414
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:12,220
We got pictures as a present from the teacher recently.

415
00:37:12,220 --> 00:37:14,980
So let's leave this moment in the pictures.

416
00:37:14,980 --> 00:37:17,440
I don't want to.

417
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:20,080
Don't take it.

418
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:25,500
- Cheese!
- I said don't take it.

419
00:37:25,500 --> 00:37:28,480
- That good, good.
- That's enough.

420
00:37:32,100 --> 00:37:35,310
- A scene angle. Let's take one together.
- Stop taking it already.

421
00:37:37,860 --> 00:37:40,150
Smile, smile.

422
00:37:43,600 --> 00:37:46,760
Hey! what was that?

423
00:37:46,760 --> 00:37:49,520
Hey! What was that?

424
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:54,200
Ha Na!

425
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:59,480
You must know this before you leave.

426
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:04,240
If it is necessary for you,

427
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:06,640
I am always in favor of it.

428
00:38:08,420 --> 00:38:10,340
Thank you.

429
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:18,220
Face, face.

430
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:26,120
You made the right decision. It will be another awesome opportunity for you, Team Leader Oh, won't it?

431
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:29,860
I will do my best before I return.

432
00:38:40,130 --> 00:38:43,750
- Congratulations!
- Thank you.

433
00:39:01,500 --> 00:39:06,270
If Assistant Manager Hong studies these materials for a year, you shouldn't have any problems catching on.

434
00:39:06,270 --> 00:39:10,210
I am envious and disappointed too.

435
00:39:10,210 --> 00:39:12,150
Thank you.

436
00:39:12,150 --> 00:39:18,510
Here! Since you are new, study from the basics and support Assistant Manager Hong well.

437
00:39:18,510 --> 00:39:23,350
Yeah. I think people like you, Team Leader Oh, are the most awesome.

438
00:39:23,350 --> 00:39:25,250
Thanks.

439
00:39:53,170 --> 00:39:58,050
Indeed you are smart. Who would have thought you'd make me a counter offer?

440
00:39:59,810 --> 00:40:02,770
Thank you for accepting it.

441
00:40:02,770 --> 00:40:07,490
I enjoy investing in order to conquer something I like.

442
00:40:07,490 --> 00:40:10,330
Oh Ha Na's decision comes first.

443
00:40:11,030 --> 00:40:15,030
I made the decision based on her performance evaluation with Jumei Global.

444
00:40:15,030 --> 00:40:20,630
I know that. I asked you because I needed it.

445
00:40:20,630 --> 00:40:26,910
In that need... I am included in there too, right?

446
00:40:28,710 --> 00:40:30,690
Yeah.

447
00:40:31,850 --> 00:40:35,290
I should see Oh Ha Na.

448
00:40:51,650 --> 00:40:54,730
Of course, our meeting is not pleasant,

449
00:40:54,730 --> 00:40:59,270
but we didn't have any unpleasant incident either, did we?

450
00:40:59,990 --> 00:41:01,870
No.

451
00:41:01,870 --> 00:41:06,070
I normally get involved in acquiring talent.

452
00:41:06,850 --> 00:41:10,270
I heard about your evaluation from Jumei.

453
00:41:10,270 --> 00:41:13,690
You are quite talented, Team Leader Oh Ha Na.

454
00:41:13,690 --> 00:41:14,910
Thank you.

455
00:41:14,910 --> 00:41:18,070
I heard you are being transferred to Jumei's branch office in Paris.

456
00:41:18,070 --> 00:41:19,710
That is correct.

457
00:41:19,710 --> 00:41:24,570
I am thinking about assigning Top Classic sponsored concerts and related Cha Seo Hoo concerts

458
00:41:24,570 --> 00:41:26,300
to you.

459
00:41:26,300 --> 00:41:29,630
What? This is the first time I am hearing about that.

460
00:41:29,630 --> 00:41:34,530
I will make Jumei Global aware of it soon.

461
00:41:34,530 --> 00:41:41,010
Moreover, what I like the most about you is the fact that you broke up with Cha Seo Hoo.

462
00:41:43,690 --> 00:41:44,750
What are you talking about?

463
00:41:44,750 --> 00:41:52,170
I am saying let's be professionals who put work before love.

464
00:41:58,700 --> 00:42:00,910
Let me ask you one thing.

465
00:42:00,910 --> 00:42:01,910
Yes.

466
00:42:01,910 --> 00:42:07,410
Did Top Classic direct Jumei Global's scout offer?

467
00:42:07,410 --> 00:42:09,470
No.

468
00:42:10,890 --> 00:42:13,750
I will ask you again.

469
00:42:13,750 --> 00:42:19,450
Was the scout offer suggested by Cha Seo Hoo?

470
00:42:24,590 --> 00:42:26,810
That is right.

471
00:42:26,810 --> 00:42:34,870
Recruiting Oh Ha Na is a condition for Cha Seo Hoo to enter into another contract with me.

472
00:42:55,590 --> 00:42:58,410
I just saw President Min.

473
00:42:58,410 --> 00:43:05,390
Is being recruited for Top Classic ... No, your suggestion?

474
00:43:08,850 --> 00:43:11,450
- Yeah.
- Why?

475
00:43:12,530 --> 00:43:15,150
Because if we work together in Paris, where we first met,

476
00:43:15,150 --> 00:43:20,530
then we can undo your words asking to end our relationship.

477
00:43:23,890 --> 00:43:29,110
No. I won't.

478
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:37,580
If you are worried about Top Classic, think of it as an extension of the work we have always been doing.

479
00:43:37,580 --> 00:43:39,960
And we can also continue with the ChaAndy line of shoe sales.

480
00:43:39,960 --> 00:43:46,220
I don't want to hear that I got my work or opportunity due to someone.

481
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:49,020
I just made a suggestion.

482
00:43:49,020 --> 00:43:52,200
You getting the opportunity is all solely because of your talent.

483
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:55,260
No one will think that.

484
00:43:59,480 --> 00:44:03,860
Teacher Park Jong Hoon will perform with me in the charity concert.

485
00:44:03,860 --> 00:44:09,720
That's nice. The concert program will be more packed than we thought.

486
00:44:11,330 --> 00:44:14,850
Dealing with my work and Seo Hoo together,

487
00:44:14,850 --> 00:44:17,720
this concert will be the last time.

488
00:44:19,900 --> 00:44:25,240
I will get up first. I will see you at the concert.

489
00:44:49,910 --> 00:44:54,490
I am getting angry. Is the reason for my anger

490
00:44:54,490 --> 00:44:58,270
because I am giving up a good opportunity,

491
00:44:58,270 --> 00:45:02,450
or is it because I confirmed the repeated separation?

492
00:45:02,450 --> 00:45:04,550
I don't know.

493
00:45:21,250 --> 00:45:22,660
Dae Bok!

494
00:45:22,660 --> 00:45:24,650
Eun Jung!

495
00:45:26,240 --> 00:45:28,910
- How about lunch?
- I already ate.

496
00:45:28,910 --> 00:45:30,650
It's hot. Why are you outside?

497
00:45:30,650 --> 00:45:35,290
It was stuffy inside. Is it because the air conditioner was on for a long time?

498
00:45:35,290 --> 00:45:37,830
Are you sick?

499
00:45:37,830 --> 00:45:39,810
I'm not sick.

500
00:45:39,810 --> 00:45:43,670
If I need to support you, I can't be sick so easily like this.

501
00:45:43,670 --> 00:45:45,450
Oh, right.

502
00:45:45,450 --> 00:45:48,670
I got the Team Leader's job.

503
00:45:48,670 --> 00:45:52,440
Since I heard she is leaving, I feel quite dejected.

504
00:45:52,440 --> 00:45:55,460
She taught me a lot and and I learned a lot from her.

505
00:45:55,460 --> 00:45:57,290
You're disappointed too, right?

506
00:45:57,290 --> 00:46:01,370
Of course. Although my noona nagged a lot,

507
00:46:01,370 --> 00:46:03,910
she took care of our family well.

508
00:46:03,910 --> 00:46:06,600
It would have been good if I had competence like Noona.

509
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:08,830
Why did my parents make me born like this?

510
00:46:08,830 --> 00:46:13,040
What's wrong with you? You're cool!

511
00:46:14,550 --> 00:46:17,090
Ah, wait.

512
00:46:31,150 --> 00:46:33,730
- How is it?
- Wow!

513
00:46:33,730 --> 00:46:36,930
It's the first time someone drew me!

514
00:46:36,930 --> 00:46:38,450
Thank you.

515
00:46:38,450 --> 00:46:40,750
I'll draw you a lot from now on.

516
00:46:55,690 --> 00:46:57,810
What are you doing, Mom?

517
00:46:59,490 --> 00:47:04,370
I was living comfortably for a little while, but now it's starting again!

518
00:47:04,370 --> 00:47:07,100
What are you going to do if you go all the way there?

519
00:47:07,100 --> 00:47:10,180
I am worried too, so please don't keep scolding me.

520
00:47:10,180 --> 00:47:15,740
Don't just look into big corporations, but rather come on out to the shop and learn the business.

521
00:47:15,740 --> 00:47:17,320
Yeah, that's right.

522
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:20,840
Didn't you say you wanted to inherit the shop?

523
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:23,810
Anyway  you are not exactly qualified for big corporations.

524
00:47:23,810 --> 00:47:27,250
Setting your dream according to your ability might seem like giving up,

525
00:47:27,250 --> 00:47:29,490
but it will give you good return in the future.

526
00:47:29,490 --> 00:47:32,310
Or just find something you really want to do and go.

527
00:47:32,310 --> 00:47:35,350
I wish I could find something I really want to do.

528
00:47:35,350 --> 00:47:37,470
Aish!

529
00:47:37,470 --> 00:47:39,370
Aigoo.

530
00:47:39,370 --> 00:47:40,830
Son!

531
00:47:40,830 --> 00:47:43,350
Here! Don't feel down!

532
00:47:43,350 --> 00:47:46,330
Put Noona's laundry in her room.

533
00:47:46,330 --> 00:47:48,110
Okay.

534
00:47:48,110 --> 00:47:49,970
Fighting!

535
00:48:16,020 --> 00:48:21,940
Summer Day
1999
Script: Choi Won

536
00:48:38,570 --> 00:48:45,800
Timing and Subtitles brought to you by The Timeless Lovers @ Viki

537
00:49:02,920 --> 00:49:04,980
So,

538
00:49:06,180 --> 00:49:08,520
open the windows

539
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:14,500
and leave the lights off? Hey, I was going to wash and sleep as soon as I got upstairs.

540
00:49:15,660 --> 00:49:17,810
What are you going to do?

541
00:49:29,950 --> 00:49:31,590
What is it?

542
00:49:39,570 --> 00:49:43,830
Something like the laser show you turned on when I  was having a hard time?

543
00:50:13,290 --> 00:50:15,430
On the day you leave,

544
00:50:15,430 --> 00:50:18,410
I can't come to the airport to say goodbye. I have a flight scheduled at night.

545
00:50:19,750 --> 00:50:21,970
Let's do this instead.

546
00:50:23,710 --> 00:50:25,790
It's far away so you might not be able to see it well, but

547
00:50:25,790 --> 00:50:30,470
these are familiar pictures to us. So you will know what they are, right?

548
00:51:10,750 --> 00:51:12,910
Remember them.

549
00:51:12,910 --> 00:51:15,310
Don't forget

550
00:51:15,310 --> 00:51:17,260
even a single moment.

551
00:51:19,860 --> 00:51:21,650
Thanks.

552
00:51:25,030 --> 00:51:27,030
Are you crying?

553
00:51:28,620 --> 00:51:32,610
No, I'm not crying.

554
00:51:32,610 --> 00:51:36,230
If you're crying, I'm going to run and go over there right now!

555
00:51:38,390 --> 00:51:40,460
I said I'm not crying.

556
00:51:55,170 --> 00:51:59,390
The way to not regret a missed opportunity

557
00:51:59,390 --> 00:52:02,250
is through the comfort of those things so very close that you do not realize their presence...

558
00:52:02,250 --> 00:52:09,030
the comfort of those trivial and precious things.

559
00:52:10,130 --> 00:52:13,730
And until the next opportunity comes,

560
00:52:13,730 --> 00:52:18,110
enduring and anticipating ...

561
00:52:32,050 --> 00:52:34,980
The event location is so pretty. Thank you.

562
00:52:34,980 --> 00:52:39,290
World Vision has donated a lot to ChaAndy line, so my father will be very happy.

563
00:52:39,290 --> 00:52:42,350
Thanks to you, it really became a global project.

564
00:52:42,350 --> 00:52:45,130
-  Work hard.
-  Okay.

565
00:52:54,490 --> 00:52:58,090
This is the last day you can relax like this.

566
00:52:58,090 --> 00:53:00,310
I'll have a lot of fun and return.

567
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:04,130
It's so small, there's no space for me here. I'll go first.

568
00:53:04,130 --> 00:53:05,570
Okay.

569
00:53:05,570 --> 00:53:07,810
Team Leader Oh.

570
00:53:12,950 --> 00:53:16,990
- I need to go because of a rehearsal.
- Okay, go ahead.

571
00:53:23,760 --> 00:53:28,270
This wouldn't compare to any other event you are going to be in-charge of in the future.

572
00:53:28,270 --> 00:53:31,810
I will not go.

573
00:53:31,810 --> 00:53:33,510
Excuse me?

574
00:53:34,940 --> 00:53:37,890
- No way.
- For a better opportunity,

575
00:53:37,890 --> 00:53:40,370
- I am postponing it.
- Okay.

576
00:53:40,370 --> 00:53:45,770
I'll accept that as you not wanting to be associated with Cha Seo Hoo anymore.

577
00:53:48,490 --> 00:53:51,210
For Seo Hoo,

578
00:53:51,210 --> 00:53:53,650
please continue to work  hard.

579
00:53:54,610 --> 00:53:58,790
That... is my job.

580
00:54:04,000 --> 00:54:07,230
- Is it all done?
- Yes. This part is almost done.

581
00:54:07,230 --> 00:54:11,190
It's almost finished. After this part is done, everything will be finished.

582
00:54:12,130 --> 00:54:16,050
This is an important concert, so I'll put my complete trust in you.

583
00:54:16,050 --> 00:54:20,570
- You asked to be assigned to be in-charge of the service training in Paris?
- Yeah.

584
00:54:20,570 --> 00:54:23,900
- I want to stay in Paris for three months.
- Why so suddenly?

585
00:54:23,900 --> 00:54:27,720
Ha Na is being transferred to Paris.

586
00:54:27,720 --> 00:54:33,130
- So you don't want to go on flights anymore and be in charge of training instead?
- Yeah.

587
00:54:33,130 --> 00:54:36,680
I think I won't be able to stand missing her.

588
00:54:36,680 --> 00:54:39,740
I want to decrease the amount of time I'm away from Ha Na.

589
00:54:41,140 --> 00:54:44,380
Alright, let's talk again.

590
00:54:46,150 --> 00:54:48,990
I have an appointment today.

591
00:54:48,990 --> 00:54:52,230
It's a date, right? Do well.

592
00:54:57,200 --> 00:55:00,850
- Everyone has worked hard.
- Everyone has worked hard!

593
00:55:13,670 --> 00:55:16,770
Thank you. It must have been a lacking stage for you, Teacher.

594
00:55:16,770 --> 00:55:21,290
Thanks to you I got to experience this. It was great.

595
00:55:21,290 --> 00:55:25,770
When you're doing your Europe tour, please come to Austria once.

596
00:55:25,770 --> 00:55:29,350
Look at you asking me to come and go. You come to me, Kid.

597
00:55:30,410 --> 00:55:34,800
You said her name was Ha Na, right? I don't see her around.

598
00:55:34,800 --> 00:55:36,640
No.

599
00:55:36,640 --> 00:55:38,020
I don't see her.

600
00:55:38,020 --> 00:55:40,620
What is it? Did you two fight?

601
00:55:40,620 --> 00:55:45,590
- How about you, teacher? You're dating well, right?
- I guess.

602
00:55:48,150 --> 00:55:51,390
Let's talk again later.

603
00:56:02,130 --> 00:56:06,330
President Min has just left the country.

604
00:56:06,330 --> 00:56:08,770
- Okay.
- She said to please leave on time.

605
00:56:08,770 --> 00:56:10,750
I said okay.

606
00:56:15,080 --> 00:56:17,160
How was the performance?

607
00:56:19,480 --> 00:56:21,670
What do you want to do now?

608
00:56:22,720 --> 00:56:27,570
I have no flights, so I should be going home.

609
00:56:27,570 --> 00:56:30,450
You're really going to go home?

610
00:56:32,030 --> 00:56:34,260
What?

611
00:56:35,590 --> 00:56:39,140
Get closer. One, two...

612
00:56:39,140 --> 00:56:43,890
- Okay, good.
- Good work!

613
00:56:47,920 --> 00:56:51,340
Please have as much as you want, the two of you.

614
00:57:01,090 --> 00:57:05,130
Where are you? I have something to say to you.

615
00:57:12,900 --> 00:57:18,240
I've already prepared the plane tickets for you and me to go to Paris.

616
00:57:20,030 --> 00:57:22,640
Please cancel them.

617
00:57:25,310 --> 00:57:30,250
If the recruiting offer wasn't associated with me,

618
00:57:30,250 --> 00:57:33,020
would you have accepted it?

619
00:57:35,020 --> 00:57:37,400
Probably.

620
00:57:37,400 --> 00:57:42,520
As we worked together, I saw you smile at other people.

621
00:57:43,700 --> 00:57:46,450
I had this thought at one point.

622
00:57:46,500 --> 00:57:51,900
You aren't smiling in my presence anymore.

623
00:57:55,470 --> 00:57:59,390
I shouldn't make it hard on you anymore, right?

624
00:58:05,670 --> 00:58:08,590
Do you know

625
00:58:10,430 --> 00:58:12,290
how much I loved you?

626
00:58:18,870 --> 00:58:23,900
I also loved you a lot.

627
00:58:32,990 --> 00:58:37,920
Then, I'll be leaving.

628
00:59:09,000 --> 00:59:12,300
One week later

629
00:59:21,390 --> 00:59:25,670
- What is that?
- Hyung Won must have sent it.

630
00:59:25,670 --> 00:59:27,620
Thanks.

631
00:59:35,500 --> 00:59:37,350
A Summer Day
Since then...

632
00:59:38,650 --> 00:59:41,390
